Whether you're just getting started with FreeBSD or you've been using it for years, you'll find this book to be the definitive guide to FreeBSD that you've been waiting for.

This book is a one-stop shop for system administrators who want to build,configure, and manage FreeBSD servers. It will also be useful for those folks
who want to run FreeBSD on their desktops, servers, diskless system farms, and so on. By the time you finish this book, you should be able to use FreeBSD to provide network services.

You should also understand how to manage, patch, and maintain your
